'''水力纺纱机'''是一种以[[水車|水車]]为动力的[[纺纱架|纺纱架]]。[[理查·阿克莱特|理查·阿克莱特]]在1769年申请了水力纺纱机的专利<ref>{{Cite web|title=Sir Richard Arkwright|url=https://www.britannica.com/biography/Richard-Arkwright|accessdate=2019-03-19|archive-date=2019-05-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190520231954/https://www.britannica.com/biography/Richard-Arkwright|dead-url=no}}</ref>，他设计了一台用于生产棉线的水力纺纱机，並於1765年首次投入使用<ref>{{Cite web|title=British History - The Textile System - The Water Frame|url=https://spartacus-educational.com/TEXframe.htm|accessdate=2019-01-09|author=John Simkin|publisher=Spartacus Educational Publishers Ltd., 1997|archive-date=2021-01-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210118235548/https://spartacus-educational.com/TEXframe.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=A History of the World - Arkwright's Water Frame spinning machine|url=http://www.dbt.co.uk/ahistoryoftheworld/objects/RyHIgvgsSeCYGZRl4Ep5RQ|accessdate=2019-01-09|publisher=BBC}}</ref>。[[理查·阿克莱特|理查·阿克莱特]]發明的水力纺纱机能够一次[[紡織|纺]]出96根线，人們通過水力紡紗機，能夠比以往任何时候都更容易、更快速的[[紡織|纺]]線。[[理查·阿克莱特|理查·阿克莱特]]的设计部分是基于阿克莱特雇佣的钟表制造商{{en-link|约翰·凯 (紡紗架)|John Kay (spinning frame)|约翰·凯}}为{{en-link|托马斯·海斯|Thomas Highs}}制造的纺纱机<ref name="McNeil1990">{{Cite book|title=An Encyclopedia of the History of Technology|last=McNeil|first=Ian|year=1990|publisher=Routledge|location=London|isbn=0415147921|pages=[https://archive.org/details/isbn_9780415147927/page/827 827]–30|url=https://archive.org/details/isbn_9780415147927}}</ref>。由于是以水力驱动，它比当时的纺纱机生产的纱线更结实、更坚硬，當時的工厂也逐步采用水力纺纱机<ref>Richard L. Hills, "Hargreaves, Arkwright and Crompton. Why Three Inventors?." ''Textile history'' 10.1 (1979): 114-126.</ref>。1770年，[[理查·阿克莱特|理查·阿克莱特]]和他的合夥人在[[德比郡|德比郡]]{{en-link|克伦福德|Cromford}}建立了一個水力紡紗廠。1771年，[[理查·阿克莱特|理查·阿克莱特]]在他位于[[德比郡|德比郡]]{{en-link|克伦福德|Cromford}}的水力紡紗廠里安裝了水力纺纱机，使得他的水力紡紗廠成為英國第一批专门为容纳机器而不是仅仅将工人聚集在一起工作的工厂<ref>The blast furnace, often considered the first continuous process, was a single process. The water frame, or more specifically the cotton mill of which it was a part, embodied a whole series of processes in one continuity, from raw cotton bale to the spun thread.</ref>。

1760年，德国漂白厂主约翰·海因里希·勃克穆爾（Johann Heinrich Bockmühl）在當時尚處於工业化初期的[[普鲁士|普鲁士]]{{en-link|埃尔伯费|Elberfeld}}（今[[德国|德国]][[伍珀塔尔|伍珀塔尔]]）也研製出另一种用于生产纺织品的水力纺纱机<ref>{{Cite web|title=Von Bleichern, Färbern und Fabrikanten|url=http://stadtgeschichte-wuppertal.de/hheyken_bilder/heyken_elberfelder_osten.pdf|accessdate=2019-01-09|author=Hinrich Heyken|publisher=City of Wuppertal|archive-date=2021-02-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210210030217/http://stadtgeschichte-wuppertal.de/hheyken_bilder/heyken_elberfelder_osten.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Industrial Heritage Expeditions - Textile in Wuppertal|url=https://www.die-bergischen-drei.de/en/tips-for-tours/industrial-heritage-expeditions/textil-im-wuppertal/stationen-in-elberfeld.html|accessdate=2019-01-09|publisher=Bergische Struktur- und Wirtschaftsförderungsgesellschaft mbH|archive-date=2019-05-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190502133402/https://www.die-bergischen-drei.de/en/tips-for-tours/industrial-heritage-expeditions/textil-im-wuppertal/stationen-in-elberfeld.html|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

